inlineContent.text: The DNS Service Discovery API helps you to perform three main tasks:
Resolving service names to host names.
In support of these main tasks, this API can directly assist you in performing two subsidiary tasks:
Updating registrations (changing your DNS registration data dynamically).
Most apps shouldn’t use this API, and instead should use a higher-level service discovery API like

. Use dnssd if you’re writing BSD-style applications or cross-platform programs that don’t need to link to higher-level frameworks. You can also use dnssd if you need specific lower-level functionality exposed by this API.
